    "ideation": "The South West Arrow is more than a direction; it is a diagonal descent. The animation personifies this as a physical and emotional 'sink' towards the bottom-left. The acting arc is a dramatic drop: the face starts high and bright in the top-right, then collapses diagonally. I am using asymmetry to create the 'arrowhead' shape—the left eye leads the dive by narrowing and pulling down-left first, while the right eye trails behind. The mouth wave mimics a sliding whistle or a falling object, decreasing in frequency and amplitude as it settles into the corner. The color shifts from a high-energy cyan to a heavy, grounded indigo to emphasize the change in 'altitude.'",
